-days\" style=\"font-size:20px\">Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter Package &#8211; 6 Days (From Dehradun)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Visit Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter with our 6-day package at just <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>INR 2,30,000<\/strong> Per Person<\/span>, All-Inclusive. Perfect for families and senior citizens, experience comfort and ease as you explore sacred destinations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Package Highlights &amp; Day Wise Itinerary:<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">5-Nights stay at scenic hotels.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">All-inclusive meals with best services.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Dedicated VIP assistance at each temple.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Benefit from the expertise of professional guides at every location.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Convenient transportation provided at each destination.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-style-default is-vertical is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-8cf370e7 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex\">\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 01 &#8211; Dehradun Arrival<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-100-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Dehradun Arrival<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Dehradun is our main base for the Heli-tours, serving as the starting and ending point.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Uttarakhand Trips offers a complimentary stay on the arrival date in Dehradun.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers are picked up from Dehradun Airport. Arrival details must be provided at the time of booking.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers should arrive in Dehradun by 2:00 PM or earlier to be ready for the Char Dham journey the next morning.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">In the evening, our team will brief the passengers and provide duffel bags for necessary items. Each person can carry up to 5 kg.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 02 &#8211; Yamunotri<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-100-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Yamunotri Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">6:30 AM <\/span>:<\/strong> Check out from Dehradun hotel<br><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">7:30 AM <\/span>: <\/strong>ETD from Sahastradhara Helidrome<br><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>8:00 AM<\/strong> <\/span>:  ETA at Kharsali Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Today marks the start of the Chardham Yatra. After an early breakfast, you&#8217;ll check out from the hotel at <strong>6:30 AM<\/strong>. <br>Our team will pick you up and take you to Sahastradhara Helidrome<strong>.<\/strong> <br><br>Once you arrive at the hotel, we&#8217;ll head straight for darshan to avoid the rush. <em>The Yamunotri Temple darshan takes about 5 hours and 30 minutes round-trip, with a 6 km trek each way.<\/em> In Kharsali, you&#8217;ll visit the hot spring at Yamunotri Temple, Yamuna Mata Temple, and Shani Temple.<\/p>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 03 &#8211; Gangotri<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Gangotri Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>8:00 AM :<\/strong> ETD from Kharsali Helipad<br><strong>8:30 AM : <\/strong>ETA at Harsil\/Jhalla Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">After breakfast, passengers will check-out by 0730 hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Arrival at Jhalla helipad will at 0830 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Jhalla \u2013<\/strong>&nbsp;After landing at Jhalla, passengers will be taken to Harsil village &amp; checked-in the hotel.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Harsil&nbsp;\u2013 <\/strong>The second destination of our tour, also known for the abundant apple orchards there, is the most scenic and beautiful destination of this tour.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Passengers will be taken for Gangotri Dham darshan before or after lunch \u2013 Depending on rush.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Approximate Time taken for Gangotri Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;3hrs 30 mins (round-trip). The road distance to Gangotri temple is approx. 25 km, which is roughly a 50-minute drive.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Sightseeing at Harsil:<\/strong>&nbsp;Bagodi Village \/ Ancient Laxmi Narayan Temple in Harsil. Other than this, Harsil also has many nearby nature-walks to explore.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 04 &#8211; Kedarnath<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Kedarnath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>8:30 AM :<\/strong> ETD from Harsil\/Jhalla Helipad<br><strong>9:00 AM : <\/strong>ETA at Sersi Heli-Base<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">After breakfast, passengers will check-out by 0730 hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Arrival at Sersi Heli-base will be at 0900 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Kedarnath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;02 hours. The shuttle services flight Sersi to Kedarnath is apporx. 07 minutes long.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Sightseeing at Sersi:<\/strong>&nbsp;Triyuginarayan Temple \u2013 It is the venue of the celestial marriage of Lord Shiva &amp; Goddess Parvati.&nbsp;(Subject to weather and road traffic conditions).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 05 &#8211; Badrinath<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Badrinath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>6:00 AM : <\/strong>ETD from Sersi Heli-Base<br><strong>6:30 AM : <\/strong>ETA at Badrinath Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Passengers will check-out by 0500\/0530 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Arrival at Badrinath will be 0630 hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Passengers will first check-in to the hotel and have breakfast. Darshan and sight-seeing will be done after breakfast or lunch \u2013 Depending on rush.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Badrinath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;Approx. 01-1.5 Hrs. Passengers will be taken from hotel to the temple by car.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Sightseeing at Badrinath:<\/strong>&nbsp;Mana Village \u2013 Known as the \u2018First village of India\u2019, due to its proximity to the China border.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 06 &#8211; Return to Dehradun<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Return to Dehradun<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>6:30 AM :<\/strong> ETD from Badrinath Helipad<br><strong>7:30 AM :<\/strong> ETA at Sahastradhara Helidrome<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Passengers will check-out by 0530\/0545 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">On arrival, our team will receive the passengers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Then passengers will be taken to the Dehradun hotel to collect their luggage from cloak rooms, and then have breakfast.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Later they\u2019ll be dropped at the airport, where we bid farewell to the passengers.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons has-custom-font-size is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-ad2f72ca wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"font-size:12px\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-fill\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background wp-element-butto