igure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"kedarnath-badrinath-yatra-by-helicopter-4-days\" style=\"font-size:20px\">Do Dham Yatra by Helicopter &#8211; 4 Days (From Dehradun)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Do Dham Yatra by Helicopter is a 4-day spiritual retreat to Kedarnath (1N) &amp; Badrinath(1N) at just INR 1,40,000 Per Person. Ideal for families and senior citizens.<br><br><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Package Highlights &amp; Day Wise Itinerary:<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">1 Night complimentary stay at Dehradun.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">2 Night comfortable stay at Kedarnath &amp; Badrinath<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Experience VIP Darshan at each temple. <\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Shri Kedarnath ji helicopter shuttle services: <em>Sersi \u2013 Kedar &#8211; Sersi.<\/em><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Benefit from the expertise of professional guides at every location.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Convenient transportation provided at each destination.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-style-default is-vertical is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-8cf370e7 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex\">\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 01 &#8211; Dehradun Arrival<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-100-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Dehradun Arrival<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Dehradun is our main base for the Heli-tours, serving as the starting and ending point.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Uttarakhand Trips offers a complimentary stay on the arrival date in Dehradun.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers are picked up from Dehradun Airport. Arrival details must be provided at the time of booking.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers should arrive in Dehradun by 2:00 PM or earlier to be ready for the Char Dham journey the next morning.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">In the evening, our team will brief the passengers and provide duffel bags for necessary items. Each person can carry up to 5 kg.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 02 &#8211; Kedarnath<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Kedarnath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>11:15 AM :<\/strong> Check out from Dehradun hotel<br><strong>12:30 PM :<\/strong> ETD from Sahastradhara Helidrome<br><strong>01:00 PM :<\/strong> ETD from Sahastradhara Helidrome<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">This is the starting day of the Dodham yatra. Passengers will check-out from the hotel at 11:15 am, after breakfast.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will report at Sahastradhara Helidrome by 1130 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">In case flight is getting delayed due to NOTAM\/delayed clearances\/bad weather etc., we shall convey to the passengers in advance, so that they may report according to the delayed timings at the Helidrome.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will be ferried to Kedarnath Dham for darshan in a shuttle services flight.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Kedarnath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;02 hours.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">The shuttle services flight Sersi to Kedarnath is apporx. 07 minutes long.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Passengers might be ferried in different shuttle services flights<\/strong>, in view of the maximum weight carrying capacity of the aircraft at a high-altitude destination such as Kedarnath.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Once the darshan is done, we will bring down passengers to Sersi.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Sightseeing at Sersi:<\/strong>&nbsp;Triyuginarayan Temple \u2013 It is the venue of the celestial marriage of Lord Shiva &amp; Goddess Parvati (Subject to weather and Road conditions).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 03 &#8211; Badrinath<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Badrinath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>01:00 PM : <\/strong>ETD from Sersi Heli-base<br><strong>01:30 PM :<\/strong> ETA at Badrinath Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will have breakfast &amp; lunch at Sersi and be ready for their flight to Badrinath by 1200 hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">On arrival at Badrinath helipad, our staff will take the passengers for hotel check-in.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will be taken for darshan to Badrinath temple in the afternoon.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Badrinath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;Approx. 01-1.5 Hrs. Passengers will be taken from hotel to the temple by car.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Sightseeing at Badrinath:<\/strong>&nbsp;Mana Village \u2013 Known as the \u2018First village of India\u2019, due to its proximity to the China border.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Aarti \/ special pooja at Badrinath Temple \u2013 Swaran\/Chandi Aarti (on an additional direct payment basis at Badrinath), with extra vehicle charges.<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 04 &#8211; Return to Dehradun<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.6\"><strong>Return to Dehradun<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>01:30 PM :<\/strong> ETD from Badrinath Helipad<br><strong>02:30 PM :<\/strong> ETA at Sahastradhara Helidrome<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will have breakfast &amp; lunch by 1230 hrs and be ready for their flight to Sahastradhara Helidrome by 1245 hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Estimated time of arrival will be 1430 hrs at Sahastradhara. On arrival, our team will be present to receive the passengers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Then passengers will be taken to the Dehradun hotel to collect their luggage from cloak rooms.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Later passengers will be dropped to the airport\/railway stations, where we bid them farewell.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/details>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons has-custom-font-size is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-ad2f72ca wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"font-size:12px\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-fill\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/Package\/kedarnath-badrinath-tour-by-helicopter\/\" style=\"background-color:#0d6eff\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">See Details<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline is-style-outline--8\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"tel:+919990383938\">Call to Reserve<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide\"\/>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\" id=\"jump-here-3\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"628\" src=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4.png\" alt=\"Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter \" class=\"wp-image-3649\" srcset=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4.png 1200w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-1024x536.png 1024w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-512x268.png 512w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-920x481.png 920w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/Char-Dham-Yatra-by-Heli-4-150x79.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"kedarnath-badrinath-yatra-by-helicopter-1-day\" style=\"font-size:20px\">Do Dham Yatra by Helicopter &#8211; Same Day Tour (From Dehradun)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Do Dham Yatra by Helicopter, a single-day tour to Kedarnath &amp; Badrinath priced at just <strong>INR 1,30,000<\/strong> per person. Offering the perfect blend of safety, reliability, and comfort, this journey ensures a seamless experience to two of India\u2019s most revered shrines.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Package Highlights &amp; Day Wise Itinerary:<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Flying from Dehradun to Kedarnath Ji, Badrinath Ji &amp; back.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Experience VIP Darshan at each temple. <\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Shri Kedarnath ji helicopter shuttle services: <em>Sersi \u2013 Kedar &#8211; Sersi.<\/em><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Refreshments at Sersi &amp; Lunch at Dehradun.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Benefit from the expertise of professional guides at every location.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<details class=\"wp-block-details is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow\" style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:700\"><summary>Day 01 &#8211; Kedarnath &amp; Badrinath<\/summary>\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1\"><strong>Kedarnath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>05:30 AM :<\/strong> ETD from Sahastradhara Helidrome<br><strong>06:00 AM : <\/strong>ETA at Sersi Heli-base<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers will report at Sahastradhara Helidrome by 0430 Hrs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">In case flight is getting delayed due to NOTAM\/delayed clearances\/bad weather etc., we shall convey to the passengers in advance, so that they may report according to the delayed timings at the Helidrome.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Passengers might be ferried in different shuttle services flights, in view of the maximum weight carrying capacity of the aircraft at a high-altitude destination such as Kedarnath.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Kedarnath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;02 hours.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">The shuttle services flight Sersi to Kedarnath is apporx. 07 minutes long.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">Once the darshan is done, passengers will be back to Sersi for refreshments.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:1px\"><strong>Badrinath Dham<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>09:00 AM : <\/strong>ETD from Sersi Heli-base<br><strong>09:30 AM : <\/strong>ETA at Badrinath Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">On arrival at Badrinath helipad, our team will take the passengers for darshan.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>Approximate time taken for Badrinath Temple Darshan:<\/strong>&nbsp;Approx. 01-1.5 Hrs. Passengers will be taken to the temple by car.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400\">After darshan, passengers will be brought back to Badrinath helipad for their flight to Sahastradhara Helidrome.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-gray-50-background-color has-background\" style=\"font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:1px\"><strong>Return to Dehradun<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><strong>11:00 AM :<\/strong> ETD from Sersi Heli-base<br><strong>12:00 PM :<\/strong> ETA at Badrinath Helipad<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Estimated time of arrival will be 1200 Hrs at Sahastradhara.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>On arrival, our team will be present to receive the passengers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Our team will arrange a lunch for the passengers at Dehradun. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n<\/details>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons has-custom-font-size is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-ad2f72ca wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\" style=\"font-size:12px\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-fill\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-background wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/Package\/kedarnath-badrinath-same-day-tour-by-helicopter\/\" style=\"background-color:#0d6eff\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">See Details<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline is-style-outline--9\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"tel:+919990383938\">Call to Reserve<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"300\" src=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta.png\" alt=\"best travel agency for char dham yatra\" class=\"wp-image-4724\" srcset=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta.png 1000w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta-300x90.png 300w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta-768x230.png 768w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta-512x154.png 512w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta-920x276.png 920w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/travel-vaidya-ta-150x45.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"payment-terms-for-charter-tours\" style=\"font-size:20px\">Payment Terms for Chardham yatra by Helicopter<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">The booking is to be done in advance with a <strong>deposit of 50%<\/strong> of the total amount.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Balance payment will be taken <strong>30 days prior<\/strong> to the date of arrival at Dehradun.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"color: var(--cs-color-entry-content); font-family: var(--cs-font-post-content-family), sans-serif; font-size: var(--cs-font-post-content-size); font-weight: var(--cs-font-post-content-weight); letter-spacing: var(--cs-font-post-content-letter-spacing); font-style: var(--cs-font-base-style);\">Passengers will not be permitted to board or commence the tour unless full &amp; and final payment of the tour has been made.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"cancellation-policy-for-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter\" style=\"font-size:20px\">Cancellation Policy for Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"300\" src=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2.png\" alt=\"cancellation policy for char dham by helicopter tours\" class=\"wp-image-5501\" srcset=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2.png 1000w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2-300x90.png 300w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2-768x230.png 768w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2-512x154.png 512w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2-920x276.png 920w, https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Experience-Himalayan-Pilgrimage-2-150x45.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"cancellation-policy-due-to-bad-weather\" style=\"font-size:20px\"><strong>Cancellation Policy Due to Bad Weather:<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">If flights are canceled due to bad weather or reasons beyond our control, refunds follow our policy.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">No compensation for extra expenses incurred due to flight cancellations.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">No flight revalidation to the next day.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Passengers wanting to rebook must make fresh bookings.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Any balance from the previous booking can be adjusted.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Tour disruptions prompt revised itineraries within the original schedule.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Extensions only considered at an extra cost and operational feasibility.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Additional night stay charges payable directly to hotels during delays.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Stuck at Kedarnath due to weather? Accommodation costs covered by passengers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Extra helicopter flights after the tour charged separately.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Stuck due to weather and want to cancel? Transportation arranged but at your expense, no refund.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"hotel-stays-during-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter-tour\">Hotel Stays During Char Dham Yatra By Helicopter Tour<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">During Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter tour, enjoy comfortable stays at select hotels offering <strong>scenic views<\/strong> of the surrounding mountains and temples. With convenient locations in <strong>Harsil (Gangotri)<\/strong>, <strong>Kharsali (Yamunotri)<\/strong>, and <strong>Badrinath<\/strong>, these hotels provide essential amenities and a relaxing environment, making your pilgrimage experience both pleasant and restful.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Dehradun <\/strong>&#8211; Hyatt Centric or Fairfield by Marriott<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Yamunotri <\/strong>&#8211; Hotel Holy Yamuna<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Gangotri <\/strong>&#8211; Harsil Retreat or Harsil Cottages<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li> <strong>Guptkashi <\/strong>&#8211; Sersi Heights <\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Badrinath <\/strong>&#8211; Hotel Lords Palace<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"best-time-to-visit-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter\">Destinations Covered in 4 Dham by Helicopter Tour<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Yamunotri Ji:<\/strong>&nbsp;The 4 Dham by helicopter tour begins at Yamunotri, with a helipad at Kharshali Village. The temple, dedicated to Goddess Yamuna, marks the origin of the Yamuna River. Pilgrims believe a dip in the holy waters grants purity and salvation, making it a sacred start to your 4 Dham helicopter tour.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Gangotri Ji:<\/strong>&nbsp;Next is Gangotri, accessible via Harshil helipad. The temple honors Goddess Ganga, with the Ganges\u2019 origin nearby. Known for its spiritual power and ever-pure waters, a visit to Gangotri is central to any Chardham Yatra by helicopter.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Kedarnath Ji:<\/strong>&nbsp;Located at 3,583 meters, Kedarnath is reached via helipads at Sirsi, Phata, or Guptkashi. The temple, a Jyotirlinga of Lord Shiva, is one of the most powerful sites on the helicopter Char Dham Yatra. It was revived by Adi Shankaracharya in the 8th century and is steeped in mythological significance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Badrinath Ji:<\/strong>&nbsp;Concluding the yatra is Badrinath, dedicated to Lord Vishnu and part of both the Char Dham and Chota Char Dham circuits. Located at 3,100 meters, the shrine is just 1 km from the helipad. Highlights include the Maha Abhishek in the morning and Shyan Aarti at night.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"best-time-to-visit-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter-1\">Best Time to visit Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">The best time to visit Char Dham by helicopter is from May to June and September to October. The weather is pleasant with clear skies ensuring smooth helicopter operations and stunning aerial views of the Himalayas. Senior citizens are recommended to visit during May &amp; June as the weather is favorable.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Clear Weather<\/strong>: May to June and September to October offer stable weather conditions with minimal rain, ensuring safe and smooth helicopter operations.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Stunning Views<\/strong>: Clear skies during these months provide breathtaking aerial views of the Himalayas and surrounding landscapes.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Pleasant Temperatures<\/strong>: Moderate weather ensures a comfortable journey, especially for senior citizens and families.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Temple Accessibility<\/strong>: All Char Dham temples are open and fully operational, welcoming pilgrims during these peak months.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>Avoid Monsoon &amp; Winter<\/strong>: Traveling during these periods helps you bypass flight delays or cancellations caused by rain or snowfall.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"health-advisory-for-chardham-yatra-by-helicopter\">Health Advisory&nbsp;for Chardham Yatra by Helicopter<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Chardham Yatra by helicopter includes visits to Yamunotri, Gangotri, Kedarnath, and Badrinath, all located between 8,500 and 11,500 feet above sea level. These are high-altitude regions where oxygen levels drop and air pressure is lower than normal. Sudden changes in altitude, especially with fast helicopter movement, can lead to altitude-related health issues.<br><br>Since the helicopter tour to Char Dham is completed in just 4 to 5 days, the body may not have time to adapt. Continuous travel, short layovers, and walking uphill without rest can trigger high altitude sickness.<br><br>Acute Mountain Sickness during Char Dham travel is common when you cross 2,500 meters in altitude. Symptoms include breathing difficulty, nausea, vomiting, headache, dizziness, fatigue, weakness, appetite loss, and sleep issues.<br><br>High Altitude Cerebral Edema during Kedarnath trip is a severe condition caused by brain swelling. This can begin with confusion, blurred vision, shortness of breath, coordination problems, and body control issues. If untreated, it can become fatal within hours.<br><br>Pulmonary edema in Badrinath or Kedarnath is another critical condition. It is caused by fluid buildup in the lungs. Warning signs include dry cough, breathlessness even at rest, chest tightness, red or pink sputum, drowsiness, and irregular heartbeat.<br><br>During your Char Dham helicopter journey, move slowly, rest after landing, eat light food, drink enough water, and avoid alcohol or smoking. Stay covered in warm layers and keep an eye out for any symptoms.<br><br>If you have heart conditions, lung problems, asthma, or any breathing disorder, consult your doctor before booking a Char Dham helicopter tour. Share your medical background with the tour operator. Hospitals are not available at high altitudes. Medical evacuation by helicopter is possible, but it depends on the weather and landing permissions.<br><br>This advisory is for travelers planning the Do Dham or Char Dham Yatra by air. Knowing the risks and responding early helps prevent health complications and ensures a safer pilgrimage experience.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"tour-guidelines-of-char-dham-by-helicopter\">Tour Guidelines&nbsp;of Char Dham by Helicopter<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Planning to book the Char Dham by Helicopter from Dehradun by helicopter? Please read these essential travel guidelines carefully to ensure a safe and smooth pilgrimage.<br><br><strong>&nbsp;Helicopter Weight Rules &amp; Passenger Info<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>VIP Darshan is subject to temple authorities and state government rules.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Due to weight limitations in high-altitude helicopter tours, Himalayan Heli may reassign passengers across flights to ensure safe operations.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Body weight must be accurately declared during booking. Incorrect info can result in denied boarding without refund.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Flight Schedule &amp; Reporting Time<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>This is a fixed-departure helicopter yatra, and passengers must report on time as per the flight schedule.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flights may be rescheduled in case of bad weather or other force majeure conditions.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Baggage Policy for Helicopter Tour<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Only 5 kg of baggage per person is allowed. Soft duffel bags will be provided by the operator.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hard suitcases or large luggage are strictly not permitted.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extra baggage will be charged at \u20b9500\/kg, and may not be accommodated due to aircraft limitations.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Arrival &amp; Transfers<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Passengers must arrive in Dehradun by 2:00 PM a day before the yatra.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Only one airport transfer in Dehradun will be provided each for arrival and departure.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Provide your arrival and departure details while booking.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Kedarnath Shuttle Flight<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Passengers will be flown to Kedarnath ji via a shuttle flight.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Group members may be split across different flights due to weight and seat distribution.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Packing &amp; Clothing Tips<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Carry light, warm clothes such as tracksuits, kurtas, and trekking shoes.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep essential medications, especially for seniors or those with health issues.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Medical check-up is advised before traveling, especially for those with altitude-related concerns.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;ID Proof &amp; Infant Policy<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Carry valid government ID (Aadhaar\/Passport).<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Infants under 2 years (max 12 kg) travel free, but their weight counts toward total permissible group weight.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>ID proof\/birth certificate of the infant will be checked.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\"><strong>&nbsp;Other Essentials<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul style=\"font-size:15px\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li style=\"font-size:15px\">Any tax increase, temple darshan charges, or personal expenses are to be borne by passengers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Passengers must complete online Yatra registration if mandated by the authorities.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>BSNL, Airtel, and Jio work best in Harsil and Badrinath. Expect limited connectivity.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Temple timings may vary, and flight plans are adjusted accordingly for darshan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Carry prescribed medication and warm clothing\u2014temperatures drop quickly in the evenings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-to-pack-for-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter-tours\">What  to Pack for Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter Tours<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"font-size:15px\">Packing right for the Char Dham Yatra by helicopter ensures a comfortable and hassle-free journey, especially for senior citizens. Since helicopter travel has strict weight limits (usually around 5 kg per person), pack only essentials. Weather in the Himalayas is unpredictable, so layering is key. Comfortable clothing, sturdy footwear, and medical essentials should be prioritized.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#d7f8ff;font-size:15px\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uttarakhandtrips.com\/blogs\/tips-for-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Read More Here &#8211; 5 Must-Have Packing List for Char Dham Yatra by Helicopter<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"essential-packing-list-for-char-dham-yatra-by-helicopter\">Essential Packing List For Char Dham Yatra By Helicopter:<\/